.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-2-5::.
6 different games are played: billiard, scrabble, bridge, mah-jongg, backgammon, snooker
There 6 different types of food: plum, cucumber, cranberry, banana, kale, cauliflower
1. the person playing billiard is on the left of the person playing mah-jongg##1
2. the person playing bridge is on the right of the person eating cranberry##1
3. the person eating cucumber is on the right of the person eating banana##1
4. the person playing scrabble is between the person playing bridge and the person playing backgammon##2
5. the person eating cranberry is on the right of the person playing mah-jongg##1
6. the person eating cauliflower is on the left of the person eating banana##1
7. the person eating plum is on the left of the person playing snooker##1
8. the person playing backgammon is on the far right##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1      |     2     |    3    |   4    |   5   |    6     |
| Game   | billiard   | mah-jongg    | snooker | bridge | scrabble | backgammon   |
| Food         | kale | plum | cranberry | cauliflower | banana  | cucumber |

